<collectingCountry id="3AB3E9E4FF83C106B85B26E4FE67F81A" box="[359,426,1944,1970]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="80606796FF83C106B88526E4FDC1F81A" box="[441,524,1944,1970]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Xizang</collectingRegion>
[
<collectingRegion id="80606796FF83C106BB2526E4FD90F81B" box="[537,605,1944,1971]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Tibet</collectingRegion>
]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0ABEFAFFFF83C106B9FB26C1FE17F853" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="421BA974FF83C106B9FB26C1FE17F853" blockId="13.[151,1437,792,2043]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF83C106B9FB26C1FE83F87F" bold="true" box="[199,334,1981,2007]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="70D07566FF83C106BA6126C1FC40F87E" box="[861,909,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">par-</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="85A4D2F7FF83C106BAF826C0FBE5F87E" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[964,1064,1980,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Torodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sortilega">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF83C106BAF826C0FBE5F87E" box="[964,1064,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">sortilega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to the similarity of the new species and 
<taxonomicName id="85A4D2F7FF83C106B868269DFE19F852" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[340,468,2016,2042]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Torodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sortilega">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF83C106B868269DFE19F852" box="[340,468,2016,2042]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">T. sortilega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
